This support for liberalisation is all the more surprising given that the attempts to establish freight corridors have not yet borne fruit save in the context of cooperation.
Europe needs to learn from experience.
It also needs a public rail service it can be proud of.
In our opinion, this is what is at stake.
Lastly, while I agree with MrÂ Jarzembowskiâs idea that the rail package constitutes a whole, and while we all agree on promoting rail transport, and moving forward in this direction, I do not think this necessarily entails liberalisation.
