Â Â  MrÂ President, I should like firstly to express my pleasure at the fact that, after a long fight and a long journey, we have finally been able to make reason prevail and have saved the budget line relating to the prevention and combating of forest fires.
Following the summer of fires that we have experienced, particularly in Portugal, I think it would have been the last straw â and no doubt a disgrace â if the European Parliament had not shown its solidarity with all of Europeâs foresters who are subject to these risks of fire.
